.TH "set_disk_ro" 9 "set_disk_ro" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
set_disk_ro \- set a gendisk read-only
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" set_disk_ro
.BI "(struct gendisk *disk "  ","
.BI "bool read_only "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "disk" 12
gendisk to operate on
.IP "read_only" 12
true to set the disk read-only, false set the disk read/write
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is used to indicate whether a given disk device should have its
read-only flag set. \fBset_disk_ro\fP is typically used by device drivers to
indicate whether the underlying physical device is write-protected.
